11:05 AM   Attorney Dan Tombasco appeared for the State. DE appears by video from MMHI with Atty William Michel. HYBRID hearing. DE's father present.Clerk P. Scypta.  
MINUTES:  Parties have rec'd reports and stipulate to doctor's findings. Court finds DE competent to proceed. Atty Michel makes motion to modify bond to signature so the DE may participate in programming in Racine Co. Representative from MMHI describes programming for the parties and Court. Discussion held. ST does not object to modification, though requests should the DE leave programming discussed on the record, the $1000 cash bond be immediately reinstated. Court modifies bond to $1000 signature. Conditions remain as set, though additional condition added: DE shall participate in the SAIL Program in Racine Co. Should DE for any reason fail to participate in programming as ordered, Court shall be immediately notified and cash bond shall be reinstated. STC set for 10/14/22 @ 11:30am.

Defendant Macy A Zeller in court, in custody.  Attorney Jessica L. Krejcarek appeared for the Prosecution.  Clerk JT  Minutes:    SPD has been unable to appoint an attorney for DE for today's hearing. Court holds colloquy with DE re: proceeding pro se or waiving time to allow SPD to appoint an attorney.  DE proceeds pro se waives right to an attorney for today's hearing.    ST called witness KSD Dep Keith Kirwan; sworn in and testified; cross-examination by DE.  DE sworn in and testified; cross by Atty Krejcarek.  ST rested and moved for bind over; arguments heard. Probable cause found; bound over for trial. Information filed; reading waived. Not guilty pleas entered. Bond continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 16, 2022 at 10:00 am.  Jury selection scheduled for April 4, 2022 at 09:00 am.
